- The main structure consists of a cyclic compound with the chemical formula C6H11N, which represents the ring structure of the molecule.
- Attached to this cyclic compound are two side chains: one containing a nitrogen atom (representing the -CNCC- group) and the other containing an oxygen atom (representing the -CO- group).
- The overall molecular formula can therefore be represented as C6H11N + C4H9NO2.

In conclusion, the molecular formula of C1CC(CC1CNCC(CO)O)O can be expressed as C10H20N2O2.
